Dimitrov went on to take the set, but Baghdatis won the third and looked on course to beat a top-20 player for the first time since the 2013 US Open, only for Dimitrov to force a decider after Baghdatis received more treatment late in the fourth set.

An early break of serve gave Dimitrov control of the decider and a second break wrapped up a hard-fought victory and secured a last-16 clash with sixth seed Andy Murray or Portugal's Joao Sousa.

 

